🚀 1. What is AQS (AbstractQueuedSynchronizer)?

👉 AbstractQueuedSynchronizer

It is the foundation of most Java locks.

🧠 Core Idea
state + queue + CAS = synchronization
🔥 Used by:
ReentrantLock
Semaphore
CountDownLatch
ReentrantReadWriteLock
⚙️ 2. Internal Structure
🔹 1. State
volatile int state;

👉 Represents:

Lock held (0/1)
Permit count
etc.
🔹 2. CLH Queue (VERY IMPORTANT)

Threads waiting are stored in a queue:

Head → T1 → T2 → T3 → Tail

Each node:

class Node {
    Thread thread;
    Node prev;
    Node next;
}
🔄 3. Lock Acquisition Flow
Step-by-step:
1. Try CAS(state)
2. If success → done
3. If fail → enqueue
4. Park thread
5. When unparked → retry
💻 Simplified Code
while (!tryAcquire()) {
    enqueue();
    LockSupport.park();
}
🔓 4. Unlock Flow
1. Release state
2. Unpark next thread
